==Sports==
Sports contested during the 1982 Commonwealth Games included [[Athletics at the 1982 Commonwealth Games|athletics]], [[Archery medal winners at the 1982 Commonwealth Games|archery]], [[Badminton at the 1982 Commonwealth Games|badminton]], [[lawn bowls]], [[boxing]], [[Cycling at the 1982 Commonwealth Games|cycling]], [[Shooting sports|shooting]], [[Swimming at the 1982 Commonwealth Games|swimming]], [[diving (sport)|diving]], [[Powerlifting|weightlifting]] and [[wrestling]].<ref name="b150s">{{cite book |title=Brisbane 150 Stories |author=McBride, Frank|year=2009 |publisher=Brisbane City Council Publication |isbn=978-1-876091-60-6|pages=274–275|display-authors=etal}}</ref> [[Table tennis]] and [[Australian football]] were demonstration sports.<ref name="official">{{cite web | url = http://www.priu.gov.lk/ProvCouncils/ProvicialCouncils.html | title = Provincial Councils | work = The Official Website of the Government of Sri Lanka | date = 3 September 2010 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090707214924/http://www.priu.gov.lk/ProvCouncils/ProvicialCouncils.html | archivedate = 7 July 2009 | df = dmy-all}}</ref>

