=== Mascot ===
{{main|Matilda (mascot)}}
The Matilda mascot from the opening ceremony was relocated to [[Wet'n'Wild Gold Coast|Wet'n'Wild Water World]], a water park in the [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]] hinterland. Unfortunately, in 2007, Matilda lay out the back of Wet'n'Wild in pieces, until 2011, when the winking icon found a new home at the back of the [[Kybong, Queensland|Kybong]] Matilda fuel station (now a [[Puma Energy]] station), near [[Gympie]], and has been thrilling visitors and locals with her impressive stature.<ref>{{cite web|last=Peters |first=Daniel |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3184575/Should-Matilda-bring-wink-Iconic-giant-kangaroo-mascot-1982-Commonwealth-Games-overlooks-nondescript-servo-make-comeback-games-return-Queensland-2018.html |title='Winking Matilda' from 1982 Commonwealth Games sits outside a service station &#124; Daily Mail Online |website=Dailymail.co.uk |date=2015-08-04 |accessdate=2016-08-28}}</ref>

== Legacy ==
In 2009 as part of the [[Q150]] celebrations, the 1982 Commonwealth Games were announced as one of the [[Q150 Icons]] of Queensland for its role as a "Defining Moment".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://statements.qld.gov.au/statement/id/64301|title=PREMIER UNVEILS QUEENSLAND’S 150 ICONS|last=Bligh|first=Anna|authorlink=Anna Bligh|date=10 June 2009|website=|publisher=[[Queensland Government]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170524033717/http://statements.qld.gov.au/statement/id/64301|archive-date=24 May 2017|dead-url=|access-date=24 May 2017}}</ref>

