{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = BAYS Center | image = | location = [[Bacolod]], [[Negros Occidental]], [[Philippines]] | owner = Bacolod City Government | surface = 1 hectare | tenants = | seating_capacity = 1,000+ }}
The '''Bacolod Arts and Youth Sports Center''' ('''BAYS Center''') is a multi-use [[gym]] located in [[Bacolod]], fronting the [[Bacolod Public Plaza]], in [[Negros Occidental]], [[Philippines]]. It is used mostly for [[basketball]], [[karatedo]] and [[boxing]] matches, and was used in events in the city like the [[MassKara Festival]] activities and other government related activities like seminars, business and political gatherings.<ref>''Mayor Speech at BAYS Center,''[http://www.visayandailystar.com/2006/October/20/topstory3.htm Visayan Daily Star], October 20, 2006 edition</ref>
It was the venue of the [[UMA-ONEBA]] and NOKAF Championships in which the [[Western Visayas]] athletes participated in sporting events.<ref>''Karatedo at BAYS Center,''[http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/bac/2003/07/15/sports/karatedo.tourney.set.html Sun Star], July 15, 2003 edition</ref><ref>''Martial arts showdown at BAYS Center,''[http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/bac/2005/02/10/sports/jins.gather.for.showdown.htmlSun Star], February 10, 2005 edition</ref>
The gym has a seating capacity of more than a thousand. It is officially designated as the [[Commission on Elections (Philippines)|COMELEC]] tally headquarters for both local and [[nation]]al [[election]] in the [[Philippines]].<ref>''Election at BAYS Center,''[http://www.visayandailystar.com/2007/April/27/topstory2.htm Visayan Daily Star], April 27, 2007 edition</ref>
Aside from the gym, it also serves as offices of the departments of the city and also serves as [[cultural]] facilities.
==External links== *[http://www.bacolodcity.gov.ph Bacolod City official website]
