{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Stade Léon-Bollée | nickname = | image = [[File:StadeLéonBollée.JPG|250px]] | fullname = Stade omnisports Léon Bollée | location = Rue Claircigny, 72000 , [[Le Mans]], [[France]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = 1904 | opened = 1906 | renovated = | expanded = 2004 | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = [[Grass]] | architect = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = <center>[[Le Mans UC72]] ([[Ligue 1]]) | seating_capacity = 17,801 | dimensions = }} '''Stade Léon-Bollée''' was a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Le Mans]], [[France]]. It is used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and was the home stadium of [[Le Mans UC72]] until 2011, when it was replaced by [[MMArena]]. The stadium is able to hold 17,801 people and was built in 1906.
